response.stringValue: When you are allergic to something, your body makes an antibody called IgE. Allergies can trigger your asthma and make it worse

People with difficult-to-control allergic asthma may find that a treatment known as "anti-IgE" biologic treatment will reduce their asthma attacks. There is one approved anti- IgE drug available in the U.S. at this time: omalizumab (brand name Xolair)
